column5: Well I've enjoyed the old photo's other's have posted on here, so after picking out some of the old ones I'm going to take to my dad's funeral, I thought I'd post a few here.  Here's a couple that I thought were pretty cool.  Dad with a bass and an old boat.  It says 1959 (before my time   )    Another 1959 one, dad on the dock with a beer    Must have been the same roll of film, Aug 1959.    This was later than 59, probably when I was about 3 maybe, so probably 1967, by the rapids in Minden (Daddy's little girl).    Hope you enjoy them.  Joey
Thank you for sharing these during this time in your life Joey.  Sincerely,  Splashhopper
Great photos Joey. Thanks.

Its quite amazing seeing the contrasting photos from yesteryear to present, it is very humbling and should remind us all of where we are going and just how temporary this life is. Very humbling indeed, cause for reflection.
cool pics. Cool shirt.  Wearing a USSR shirt in 1959 is pretty gutsy.  lol. I love old pics.
mmmmm Red Cap ! lol  Nice shots Hun !
Yup, nice shot Joey.. thanks for sharing
I like old pictures.  Thanks for sharing.
nice photos
Daddy's little girl .... how precious is that ? Yup.  I did enjoy them.  Thanks Joey.
The Cold War didn't really start to heat-up until the 60's. Sorry for the pun.
Really great shots Joey... Daddy's little girl is making me veklempt! HH
Very cool Joey, thanks for sharing. I have many boxes of old photo's from the 40's, 50's and 60's, some earlier, that I need to go through and put in albums. Thanks for the inspiration.
Very nice Joey.  Think I should try to dig up some old pics too.  Thanks
SMOOOOOOOOOOOOOLIE!
Joey, those are some awesome pics!   I hope they can put a smile on your face
Dudette I wanna dig up some pictures of my sis.   You look just like her... and you were a lip bitter too!!  Such a cutie...  Wha Happen??!!  HD
Very cool pics Joey, thanks for posting.
Thanks for sharing Joey!!! Cool pics Leechman
Thats one handsome fella in the 3rd shot J. Thanks for sharing.
